race.comment: PRIVATE EYE (2) returns to Caulfield having won the G2 PB Lawrence over this route easily fresh. Two runs since have been solid, only run down by Pericles in the G2 Tramway as a heavily supported favourite two back, then trying hard out to a mile behind Fangirl and Lindermann last time. That's the best form in this race, he'll roll forward with regular jockey Nash Rawiller down to ride and should take a power of beating. HERE TO SHOCK (1) might be the danger at each way odds. He was third in that Lawrence fresh and has been okay in two runs since, lugging 58kg in the G1 Sir Rupert Clarke last time and battling on for ninth. He'll land in the first few doing no work and can improve. MEDIA WORLD (6) was a tough winner at Flemington last time out and is a horse on the up. Less suited at the weights now but has to be considered. WILLAIDOW (3) did enough fresh and has claims.
